# /feature-build: Single-Feature End-to-End Builder

The user hands you ONE feature. You take it all the way from "I want X" to
"X is built, verified, and audited". No auto-discovery. No multi-feature
queue. Maximum rigor per feature.

## How /feature-build relates to its siblings

| Skill | Features | Personas | Discovery |
|-------|----------|----------|-----------|
| **`/feature-build`** | **1 (user-specified)** | **Any — user names the target persona** | **None — user says what to build** |
| `/auto-feature-build` | Up to 5 | 1 (chosen at runtime) | Auto-discover via gap analysis |
| `/auto-feature-build-full` | Up to 10 | All | Auto-discover + cross-persona dedup |

This is the "manual, heavyweight" tier. It runs /autoplan-full by default
because the user invested the mental cost of picking one feature — they
deserve the deepest framing, research, and review.

